@johnsca @tvansteenburgh Fixed my earlier mistake. Resubmitting.

- Fixing memory leak in the `extrinsics_graph` class, when a `device` object destructed the extrinsics data were not actually cleared up.
This issue can be reproduce by the following code snippet:
```cpp
pipeline pipe;
while (true)
{
    pipe.start();
    pipe.stop();
}
```

- Fixing Linux compilation issues when setting `BUILD_EASYLOGGINGPP` flag to `false`.

This method is used in the `changelist_view` to get the changelist form.
    
You may want to override this method to serve different forms depending
on the user that make the request. For example:
    
    class MyConstanceAdmin(ConstanceAdmin):
        def get_changelist_form(self, request):
            if request.user.is_superuser:
                return SuperuserForm:
            else:
                return super(MyConstanceAdmin, self).get_changelist_form(request)

Django's `ModelAdmin` has similar hooks which are pretty useful when you need to allow different groups of users with different privileges to access the admin site.

I'm a little surprised that the cloudpickle modifications no longer seem to be necessary. I thought we needed those changes in order to pickle remote functions that invoked other remote functions.

@mehrdadn, do you remember any examples of functions that can't be pickled normally by cloudpickle but that could be pickled with the augmented version? I can't seem to recreate such an example at the moment.

The problem probably still exists, so if that's the case we should see if we can create a patch for cloudpickle.
